        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 6 at 3:53PM EDT by NWS Jackson KY</headline>
        <description>At 353 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Shoal, or 8 miles northwest of Hyden, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hazard, Hyden, Buckhorn, Avawam, Hosea, Saul, Sizerock, Dryhill,
Shoal, Toulouse, Kaliopi, Krypton, Brutus, Confluence, Gays Creek,
Wooton, Mosley Bend, Chavies, Thousandsticks, and Panco.

THIS INCLUDES Hal Rogers Parkway between mile markers 39 and 57.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
